    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;To aid debugging, HTTP caches often append header fields to a response, explaining how they handled the request in an ad hoc manner.  This specification defines a standard mechanism to do so that is aligned with HTTP's caching model.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
